keyFacts: Ghislaine Maxwell had 203 recorded travel encounters with U.S. Customs and Border Protection between 2000 and June 2019.
Her travel patterns show frequent transatlantic flights between the U.S. (especially Boston, New York, Miami) and London, as well as travel to Caribbean destinations.
The document shows use of both commercial airline flights and private aircraft (indicated by tail numbers like N17ND, N923CL, 909JE).
The data was generated on September 23, 2019, indicating law enforcement was actively reviewing her travel history around that time.
Maxwell's travel continued through 2019, with her last recorded entry being on June 11, 2019, at Boston Logan Airport.
